problem of evil and moral responsibility—sometimes successfully, oftentimes not. In the process, he offers a wide-ranging tour of modern American history.Taken together, Cotkin maintains, these episodes reveal that the central concepts of morality—evil, empathy, and virtue—are both necessary and troubling. Without empathy, for example, we fail to inhabit the world of others; with it, we sometimes elevate individual suffering over political complexities. For Cotkin, close historical analysis may help reenergize these concepts for ethical thinking and acting. Morality's Muddy Waters argues for a moral turn in the way we study and think about history, maintaining that even when answers to ethical dilemmas prove elusive, the act of grappling with them is invaluable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBombing, AerialxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aCapital punishmentxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aEthical problemsvCase studies. 0aEthical problemsxCase studies. 0aEthicszUnited StatesxHistoryx20th centuryxCase studies. 0aEthicszUnited StatesxHistoryx21st centuryxCase studies. 0aEthicszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th centuryvCase studies. 0aEthicszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st centuryvCase studies. 0aIraq War, 2003-2011xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMy Lai Massacre, Vietnamd968xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMy Lai Massacre, Vietnam, 1968xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aRacismxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aWorld Ward939-1945xMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 4aAmerican Studies. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aPolitical Science.  aPublic Policy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package America